<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><rss version="2.0"><channel><title>Shawn Field Notes</title><description>Learning systems, agent notes, projects, and essays from Shawn.</description><link>https://kevinwangsheng.github.io/my-blog/</link><item><title>AI coding 全部外包,现在一定会崩</title><link>https://kevinwangsheng.github.io/my-blog/essays/ai-coding-outsourcing-breaks/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://kevinwangsheng.github.io/my-blog/essays/ai-coding-outsourcing-breaks/</guid><description>生成越快,越多的判断被推给 review;而 review 恰恰是人最想外包、也最难守住的一环。全部外包给 AI,崩只是时间问题。</description><pubDate>Thu, 02 Jul 2026 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>让 agent 连跑几小时的是 harness,不是模型</title><link>https://kevinwangsheng.github.io/my-blog/essays/harness-that-runs-for-hours/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://kevinwangsheng.github.io/my-blog/essays/harness-that-runs-for-hours/</guid><description>先把 Anthropic《Build Agents That Run for Hours》这套 Planner–Generator–Evaluator harness 逐块讲清楚,再用一个真的跑了两小时、72 条准则的 3D 项目复现它——包括对抗审计怎么把&apos;纸糊的验证&apos;逼成实测,以及读 trace 怎么抓到一个&apos;绿色的假收敛&apos;。</description><pubDate>Thu, 02 Jul 2026 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>AGENTS.md 到底该写什么</title><link>https://kevinwangsheng.github.io/my-blog/essays/agents-md-is-working-boundary/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://kevinwangsheng.github.io/my-blog/essays/agents-md-is-working-boundary/</guid><description>AGENTS.md 给 coding agent 写开工边界。先讲它是什么,再用公开项目原文拆解哪些内容真的会改变 agent 的下一步动作。</description><pubDate>Fri, 19 Jun 2026 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>评审 Coding Agent：关键不是多一个 Agent，而是隔离</title><link>https://kevinwangsheng.github.io/my-blog/essays/coding-agent-eval-needs-isolation/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://kevinwangsheng.github.io/my-blog/essays/coding-agent-eval-needs-isolation/</guid><description>什么时候用 subagent、什么时候新开会话、什么时候该把评审做成正式 rubric。</description><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jun 2026 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Agent memory 不是向量库，是写入策略</title><link>https://kevinwangsheng.github.io/my-blog/essays/agent-memory-is-write-policy/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://kevinwangsheng.github.io/my-blog/essays/agent-memory-is-write-policy/</guid><description>真正有用的 agent memory 不只是保存聊天历史,而是决定什么状态值得写入、更新、选择、遗忘和审计。</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jun 2026 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Agent sandbox 是执行边界，不是安全按钮</title><link>https://kevinwangsheng.github.io/my-blog/essays/sandbox-is-execution-boundary/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://kevinwangsheng.github.io/my-blog/essays/sandbox-is-execution-boundary/</guid><description>让 agent 跑代码之前,先分清 sandbox 能隔离什么、不能替你决定什么,以及为什么凭据和网络边界仍然是产品设计问题。</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jun 2026 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Function calling 是能力，agent loop 是授权</title><link>https://kevinwangsheng.github.io/my-blog/notes/function-calling-is-not-agent-loop/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://kevinwangsheng.github.io/my-blog/notes/function-calling-is-not-agent-loop/</guid><description>给模型工具不等于让模型控制流程;多数生产系统应该先 workflow,只在必要处给 bounded loop。</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jun 2026 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>先投 harness，再谈 fine-tune</title><link>https://kevinwangsheng.github.io/my-blog/notes/harness-before-finetune/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://kevinwangsheng.github.io/my-blog/notes/harness-before-finetune/</guid><description>如果问题能通过工具、权限、上下文、评估和流程解决, fine-tune 不应该是第一反应。</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jun 2026 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>什么时候需要 microVM sandbox</title><link>https://kevinwangsheng.github.io/my-blog/notes/microvm-when-untrusted-code/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://kevinwangsheng.github.io/my-blog/notes/microvm-when-untrusted-code/</guid><description>microVM 的理由不是炫技,而是 threat model:不可信代码、多租户、强隔离和可控执行面。</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jun 2026 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Sandbox 保护 host，不保护你放进去的 secrets</title><link>https://kevinwangsheng.github.io/my-blog/notes/sandbox-protects-host-not-secrets/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://kevinwangsheng.github.io/my-blog/notes/sandbox-protects-host-not-secrets/</guid><description>隔离边界能限制失控进程,但不能替你决定哪些凭据、文件和网络权限不该进入 sandbox。</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jun 2026 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>UI agent 必须看见自己做了什么</title><link>https://kevinwangsheng.github.io/my-blog/notes/visual-verification-loop/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://kevinwangsheng.github.io/my-blog/notes/visual-verification-loop/</guid><description>截图、axe 和 Lighthouse 是最低地板,审美仍然需要人的最终验收。</description><pubDate>Sun, 14 Jun 2026 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Context engineering 是生命周期设计</title><link>https://kevinwangsheng.github.io/my-blog/essays/context-engineering-as-lifecycle/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://kevinwangsheng.github.io/my-blog/essays/context-engineering-as-lifecycle/</guid><description>上下文窗口变长并不会自动带来可靠 agent,真正重要的是写入、选择、压缩、隔离和恢复。</description><pubDate>Sat, 13 Jun 2026 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Review gate 不是拖慢 agent,而是产品设计</title><link>https://kevinwangsheng.github.io/my-blog/notes/review-gates-are-product-design/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://kevinwangsheng.github.io/my-blog/notes/review-gates-are-product-design/</guid><description>真正需要人的地方应该被设计成清晰验收点,而不是让人承担重复检查。</description><pubDate>Sat, 13 Jun 2026 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>公开知识花园需要 agent,但不能只剩 agent</title><link>https://kevinwangsheng.github.io/my-blog/essays/public-garden-with-agents/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://kevinwangsheng.github.io/my-blog/essays/public-garden-with-agents/</guid><description>个人站可以成为学习系统的公开切面:agent 降低整理摩擦,人负责边界、判断和表达。</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jun 2026 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Context engineering 不是把上下文塞满</title><link>https://kevinwangsheng.github.io/my-blog/notes/context-engineering-compression/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://kevinwangsheng.github.io/my-blog/notes/context-engineering-compression/</guid><description>上下文真正的难点是选择、压缩、隔离和恢复,而不是窗口长度。</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jun 2026 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>先有证据,再说完成</title><link>https://kevinwangsheng.github.io/my-blog/notes/evidence-before-claim/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://kevinwangsheng.github.io/my-blog/notes/evidence-before-claim/</guid><description>agent 协作里最重要的礼貌之一,是不要把推断说成已验证事实。</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jun 2026 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>AI 时代的学习不是更快读完</title><link>https://kevinwangsheng.github.io/my-blog/essays/learning-in-the-agent-era/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://kevinwangsheng.github.io/my-blog/essays/learning-in-the-agent-era/</guid><description>当 agent 能替你收集和整理材料,人的学习重心会从搬运信息转向判断、校准和表达。</description><pubDate>Tue, 09 Jun 2026 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item></channel></rss>